# Docs Wiki Workflow

When working in `Docs/`, follow the project-wiki system.

## Before Editing

- Read `.codebuddy/skills/project-wiki/SKILL.md`.
- Read `Docs/.wiki-schema.md` for page types, frontmatter, and directory rules.
- Read `Docs/00-meta/ai-playbook.md` for AI collaboration constraints.
- Use `Docs/index.md` to locate existing related pages before creating new pages.

## Content Rules

- Keep Markdown as the source of truth.
- Preserve frontmatter fields and update status metadata when relevant.
- Use explicit `[[wikilink]]` references instead of vague phrases like "see related docs".
- Prefer the teaching structure: concept intuition, technical mechanism, Lyra example.
- Do not cite `status: stale` or `status: deprecated` pages without warning the user.

## Workflow Routing

- Teaching or explanation: read `workflows/teach.md`.
- Source analysis: read `workflows/source-trace.md`.
- New tutorial series: read `workflows/create-series.md`.
- Improve existing tutorials: read `workflows/evolve-series.md`.
- Review or lint knowledge quality: read `workflows/review-series.md` or `workflows/lint.md`.

After substantial wiki edits, suggest rebuilding the wiki index incrementally rather than doing a full rebuild by default.
